                                                 ANGULAR

Basic Building Blocks


1) Module- to import 3rd party modules (root module -app.module.ts)
2) Component - to create html ts and css file

Basic Commands 
1) To create new project -- ng new project_name
2) TO create new Component-- ng g c component_name
3) To run angular file -- ng serve --open


baasic concepts

1]  Data Binding----share data between components

ts-- component
html -- view

1)one way data Binding
data sharing only one direction
       1.1)component to view (ts->html)

          a)String interpolation-{{expression}}
          b)property Binding-[attribute_name]="property"

        1.2)view to components(html ton ts )
            a)event binding--(event_name)="function_name()"
            b)event bindimg using $event-($event_name)="function_name()"
            c)Event binding using tempelate referencing variable--#variable name





        2)Two Way Databinding
          Data sharing in both direction(ts -> html     html->ts
          i)ngModel binding - import formmodule in app.module.ts
           [(ngModel)]="property_name"


 2]  Angular Routing

        To set path for component

        {
         path:value,component:component_name
        },
        
         login
         {
            path:'',component:logincomponent
        },







3]Angular services

         To hold redundant data

   to create a new service -- ng g s serve_name



 4] Dependancy Injuction
    
    share data between two dependend classes
    constructors(private ds:DataServices)

5)Angular Directives-- to manipulate DOM

  a)component directives (array)


  b)structural directives (table)
  ->*ngFor


  6)Angular forms
   
     a)Tempelate Driven forms(first design the html tempelate)
     b)Model Driven forms (first design model in ts file)
        1)Reactive forms
          formGroup,array,control
          for advanced validation
          import form Reactive Forms Module(in app.module.ts)
    


